1) Write a program to accepts two numbers from stdin and find all the odd as well as even numbers present in between them.
import java.util.Scanner;

import java.util.Scanner;
	public class acad 
	{ 
    public static void main(String args[])
	{
	Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in); 
	int a,b; 
	System.out.println("Enter the first number"); 
	a=s.nextInt(); //the user will give the first number
	System.out.println("Enter the second number:");
	b=s.nextInt(); //and now we are provided by second number from the user
	System.out.println("The even numbers are");
	for(int i=a;i<=b;i++)
	{
	if(i%2==0)//when divided by 2 and if the denominator is 0.then it is even.
	{
	System.out.println(i); 
	}
	System.out.println("The odd numbers are"); 
	for(i=a;i<=b;i++) 
	{ 
	if(i%2!=0) System.out.println(i);//when we divide the i value by 2 and if the denominator is not zero then it's odd.
	}
	} }}


We will get the first number from the user as well the second number.it will go inside the for loop.and will check whethere the given
number is divisible by 2 and the remainder is 0. if so the number will be "even". if the remainder is 1 then it will be a odd number.

